medical_history.chief_complaint: Primary amenorrhea and lack of puberty development.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The symptoms began at puberty, with no menstrual cycle or breast development observed, indicating an early onset of hormone deficiency. The proband underwent breast augmentation surgery 2 weeks prior to seeking medical attention. No changes in symptoms were reported at that time.
medical_history.past_medical_history: The patient's father had a history of unilateral cryptorchidism. Additionally, the proband's aunt and three cousins exhibited similar symptoms of sex reversal, contributing to the family history of sex reversal.
medical_history.family_history: An aunt with similar manifestations and three cousins of the father with sex reversal phenotypes.
